<item>
            <title>[FLINK-4784] MetricQueryService actor name collision</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4784</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The name of the MetricQueryService actor is currently fixed, which can lead to collisions if multiple TaskManagers run in the same actor system, as is the case for the MiniCluster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can append the TaskManager ResourceID to make the name unique for every TaskManager. The MetricFetcher would still be able to reliable infer the correct actor name.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13010951">FLINK-4784</key>
            <summary>MetricQueryService actor name collision</summary>
